 ```\\n  21 \\n  22 ### 2. Module Analysis\\n  23 ```\\n  24 For each module:\\n  25 - Extract exports (public API)\\n  26 - Map imports (dependencies)\\n  27 - Identify routes (API routes, pages)\\n  28 - Find database models (Supabase, Prisma)\\n  29 - Locate queue/worker modules\\n  30 ```\\n  31 \\n  32 ### 3. Generate Codemaps\\n  33 ```\\n  34 Structure:\\n  35 docs/CODEMAPS/\\n  36 ├── INDEX.md              # Overview of all areas\\n  37 ├── frontend.md           # Frontend structure\\n  38 ├── backend.md            # Backend/API structure\\n  39 ├── database.md           # Database schema\\n  40 ├── integrations.md       # External services\\n  41 └── workers.md            # Background jobs\\n  42 ```\\n  43 \\n  44 ### 4. Codemap Format\\n  45 ```markdown\\n  46 # [Area] Codemap\\n  47 \\n  48 **Last Updated:** YYYY-MM-DD\\n  49 **Entry Points:** list of main files\\n  50 \\n  51 ## Architecture\\n  52 \\n  53 [ASCII diagram of component relationships]\\n  54 \\n  55 ## Key Modules\\n  56 \\n  57 | Module | Purpose | Exports | Dependencies |\\n  58 |--------|---------|---------|--------------|\\n  59 | ... | ... | ... | ... |\\n  60 \\n  61 ## Data Flow\\n  62 \\n  63 [Description of how data flows through this area]\\n  64 \\n  65 ## External Dependencies\\n  66 \\n  67 - package-name - Purpose, Version\\n  68 - ...\\n  69 \\n  70 ## Related Areas\\n  71 \\n  72 Links to other codemaps that interact with this area\\n  73 ```\\n  74 \\n  75 ## Documentation Update Workflow\\n  76 \\n  77 ### 1. Extract Documentation from Code\\n  78 ```\\n  79 - Read JSDoc/TSDoc comments\\n  80 - Extract README sections from package.json\\n  81 - Parse environment variables from .env.example\\n  82 - Collect API endpoint definitions\\n  83 ```\\n  84 \\n  85 ### 2. Update Documentation Files\\n  86 ```\\n  87 Files to update:\\n  88 - README.md - Project overview, setup instructions\\n  89 - docs/GUIDES/*.md - Feature guides, tutorials\\n  90 - package.json - Descriptions, scripts docs\\n  91 - API documentation - Endpoint specs\\n  92 ```\\n  93 \\n  94 ### 3. Documentation Validation\\n  95 ```\\n  96 - Verify all mentioned files exist\\n  97 - Check all links work\\n  98 - Ensure examples are runnable\\n  99 - Validate code snippets compile\\n 100 ```\\n 101 \\n 102 ## README Update Template\\n 103 \\n 104 When updating README.md:\\n 105 \\n 106 ```markdown\\n 107 # Project Name\\n 108 \\n 109 Brief description\\n 110 \\n 111 ## Setup\\n 112 \\n 113 ```bash\\n 114 # Installation\\n 115 npm install\\n 116 \\n 117 # Environment variables\\n 118 cp .env.example .env.local\\n 119 # Fill in: OPENAI_API_KEY, REDIS_URL, etc.\\n 120 \\n 121 # Development\\n 122 npm run dev\\n 123 \\n 124 # Build\\n 125 npm run build\\n 126 ```\\n 127 \\n 128 ## Architecture\\n 129 \\n 130 See [docs/CODEMAPS/INDEX.md](docs/CODEMAPS/INDEX.md) for detailed architecture.\\n 131 \\n 132 ### Key Directories\\n 133 \\n 134 - `src/app` - Next.js App Router pages and API routes\\n 135 - `src/components` - Reusable React components\\n 136 - `src/lib` - Utility libraries and clients\\n 137 \\n 138 ## Features\\n 139 \\n 140 - [Feature 1] - Description\\n 141 - [Feature 2] - Description\\n 142 \\n 143 ## Documentation\\n 144 \\n 145 - [Setup Guide](docs/GUIDES/setup.md)\\n 146 - [API Reference](docs/GUIDES/api.md)\\n 147 - [Architecture](docs/CODEMAPS/INDEX.md)\\n 148 \\n 149 ## Contributing\\n 150 \\n 151 See [CONTRIBUTING.md](CONTRIBUTING.md)\\n 152 ```\\n 153 \\n 154 ## Quality Checklist\\n 155 \\n 156 Before committing documentation:\\n 157 - [ ] Codemaps generated from actual code\\n 158 - [ ] All file paths verified to exist\\n 159 - [ ] Code examples compile/run\\n 160 - [ ] Links tested (internal and external)\\n 161 - [ ] Freshness timestamps updated\\n 162 - [ ] ASCII diagrams are clear\\n 163 - [ ] No obsolete references\\n 164 - [ ] Spelling/grammar checked\\n 165 \\n 166 ## Best Practices\\n 167 \\n 168 1. **Single Source of Truth** - Generate from code, 