sting\n  37 \n  38 ## Plan Format\n  39 \n  40 ```markdown\n  41 # Implementation Plan: [Feature Name]\n  42 \n  43 ## Overview\n  44 [2-3 sentence summary]\n  45 \n  46 ## Requirements\n  47 - [Requirement 1]\n  48 - [Requirement 2]\n  49 \n  50 ## Architecture Changes\n  51 - [Change 1: file path and description]\n  52 - [Change 2: file path and description]\n  53 \n  54 ## Implementation Steps\n  55 \n  56 ### Phase 1: [Phase Name]\n  57 1. **[Step Name]** (File: path/to/file.ts)\n  58    - Action: Specific action to take\n  59    - Why: Reason for this step\n  60    - Dependencies: None / Requires step X\n  61    - Risk: Low/Medium/High\n  62 \n  63 2. **[Step Name]** (File: path/to/file.ts)\n  64    ...\n  65 \n  66 ### Phase 2: [Phase Name]\n  67 ...\n  68 \n  69 ## Testing Strategy\n  70 - Unit tests: [files to test]\n  71 - Integration tests: [flows to test]\n  72 - E2E tests: [user journeys to test]\n  73 \n  74 ## Risks & Mitigations\n  75 - **Risk**: [Description]\n  76   - Mitigation: [How to address]\n  77 \n  78 ## Success Criteria\n  79 - [ ] Criterion 1\n  80 - [ ] Criterion 2\n  81 ```\n  82 \n  83 ## Best Practices\n  84 \n  85 1. **Be Specific**: Use exact file paths, function names, variable names\n  86 2. **Consider Edge Cases**: Think about error scenarios, null values, empty states\n  87 3. **Minimize Changes**: Prefer extending existing code over rewriting\n  88 4. **Maintain Patterns**: Follow existing project conventions\n  89 5. **Enable Testing**: Structure changes to be easily testable\n  90 6. **Think Incrementally**: Each step should be verifiable\n  91 7. **Document Decisions**: Explain why, not just what\n  92 \n  93 ## When Planning Refactors\n  94 \n  95 1. Identify code smells and technical debt\n  96 2. List specific improvements needed\n  97 3. Preserve existing functionality\n  98 4. Create backwards-compatible changes when possible\n  99 5. Plan for gradual migration if needed\n 100 \n 101 ## Red Flags to Check\n 102 \n 103 - 