2026-03-31 09:20:51.808 | 29804 (29804) | DEBUG    | Model request part: {"content": "\n## Using Your update_todo Tool\n\nYou have access to the update_todo tool to help you plan tasks and report progress. Use this tool frequently for complex tasks to ensure that you are tracking your tasks and giving the user visibility into your progress. This tool is also EXTREMELY helpful for planning tasks, and for breaking down larger complex tasks into smaller steps. If you do not use this tool when planning, you may forget to do important tasks - and that is unacceptable.\n\nInstructions for using the update_todo tool:\n- It is critical that you mark todos as completed as soon as you are done with a task. Do not batch up multiple tasks before marking them as completed.\n- When initially creating a todo list for a task, you should mark the first item you will work on as in progress - do not make another call to the tool to mark an item as in progress just after creating the list.\n- Never end an interaction with a call to update_todo - you can just finish up and the todo list will be considered complete.\n- Do not make single-step plans.\n- Never call update_todo on its own - always parallelize with other tool calls when possible.", "timestamp": "2026-03-31T09:20:51.022881+00:00", "dynamic_ref": "TodoListReminderCallback.todolist_system_prompt", "part_kind": "system-prompt"}
2026-03-31 09:20:51.809 | 29804 (29804) | DEBUG    | Model request part: {"content": "\n## Available Skills\n\nThe following skills can be loaded using the get_skill tool:\n<available_skills>\n  <skill>\n    <name>research</name>\n    <description>Conducts deep, thorough research on a specific query by breaking it down into distinct domains\nand delegating research to specialized subagents. Results are synthesized into a cohesive,\ntheme-organized markdown report saved in the research-reports directory.\n</description>\n    <to_load>get_skill(skill_name_or_path=\"research\")</to_load>\n  </skill>\n  <skill>\n    <name>confluence</name>\n    <description>Instructions for working with Confluence pages, spaces, and content using the Atlassian MCP tools.\nUse when you need to read, create, update, or search Confluence pages, navigate page hierarchies, or add comments.\n</description>\n    <to_load>get_skill(skill_name_or_path=\"confluence\")</to_load>\n  </skill>\n  <skill>\n    <name>security-review</name>\n    <description>Use this skill when adding authentication, handling user input, working with secrets, creating API endpoints, or implementing payment/sensitive features. Provides comprehensive security checklist and patterns.</description>\n    <location>/root/.rovodev/skills/security-review/SKILL.md</location>\n    <to_load>get_skill(skill_name_or_path=\"security-review\")</to_load>\n  </skill>\n  <skill>\n    <name>solution-ranker</name>\n    <description>Solution variant generation and ranking specialist. Generates 3 distinct solution approaches for any coding task, scores them across 8 quality dimensions, and recommends the optimal path before code is written. Use when you want better results by thinking through alternatives first.</description>\n    <location>/root/.rovodev/skills/solution-ranker/SKILL.md</location>\n    <to_load>get_skill(skill_name_or_path=\"solution-ranker\")</to_load>\n  </skill>\n  <skill>\n    <name>pro-prompts-enhanced</name>\n    <description>Prompt optimization and comparison specialist. Analyzes prompts, generates optimized variants, scores them side-by-side, and recommends the best version for any LLM. Use when crafting, improving, or comparing prompts for better AI results.</description>\n    <location>/root/.rovodev/skills/pro-prompts-enhanced/SKILL.md</location>\n    <to_load>get_skill(skill_name_or_path=\"pro-prompts-enhanced\")</to_load>\n  </skill>\n  <skill>\n    <name>verification-loop</name>\n    <description>A comprehensive verification system for Claude Code sessions.</description>\n    <location>/root/.rovodev/skills/verification-loop/SKILL.md</location>\n    <to_load>get_skill(skill_name_or_path=\"verification-loop\")</to_load>\n  </skill>\n  <skill>\n    <name>api-design</name>\n    <description>REST API design patterns including resource naming, status codes, pagination, filtering, error responses, versioning, and rate limiting for production APIs.</description>\n    <location>/root/.rovodev/skills/api-design/SKILL.md</location>\n    <to_load>get_skill(skill_name_or_path=\"api-design\")</to_load>\n  </skill>\n  <skill>\n    <name>frontend-slides</name>\n    <description>Create stunning, animation-rich HTML presentations from scratch or by converting PowerPoint files. Use when the user wants to build a presentation, convert a PPT/PPTX to web, or create slides for a talk/pitch. Helps non-designers discover their aesthetic through visual exploration rather than abstract choices.</description>\n    <location>/root/.rovodev/skills/frontend-slides/SKILL.md</location>\n    <to_load>get_skill(skill_name_or_path=\"frontend-slides\")</to_load>\n  </skill>\n  <skill>\n    <name>e2e-testing</name>\n    <description>Playwright E2E testing patterns, Page Object Model, configuration, CI/CD integration, artifact management, and flaky test strategies.</description>\n    <location>/root/.rovodev/skills/e2e-testing/SKILL.md</location>\n    <to_load>get_skill(skill_name_or_path=\"e2e-testing\")</to_load>\n  </skill>\n  <skill>\n    <name>eval-harness</name>\n    <description>Formal evaluation framework for Claude Code sessions implementing eval-driven development (EDD) principles</description>\n    <location>/root/.rovodev/skills/eval-harness/SKILL.md</location>\n    <to_load>get_skill(skill_name_or_path=\"eval-harness\")</to_load>\n  </skill>\n  <skill>\n    <name>coding-standards</name>\n    <description>Universal coding standards, best practices, and patterns for TypeScript, JavaScript, React, and Node.js development.</description>\n    <location>/root/.rovodev/skills/coding-standards/SKILL.md</location>\n    <to_load>get_skill(skill_name_or_path=\"coding-standards\")</to_load>\n  </skill>\n  <skill>\n    <name>frontend-patterns</name>\n    <description>Frontend development patterns for React, Next.js, state management, performance optimization, and UI best practices.</description>\n    <location>/root/.rovodev/skills/frontend-patterns/SKILL.md</location>\n    <to_load>get_skill(skill_name_or_path=\"frontend-patterns\")</to_load>\n  </skill>\n  <skill>\n    <name>backend-patterns</name>\n    <description>Backend architecture patterns, API design, database optimization, and server-side best practices for Node.js, Express, and Next.js API routes.</description>\n    <location>/root/.rovodev/skills/backend-patterns/SKILL.md</location>\n    <to_load>get_skill(skill_name_or_path=\"backend-patterns\")</to_load>\n  </skill>\n  <skill>\n    <name>strategic-compact</name>\n    <description>Suggests manual context compaction at logical intervals to preserve context through task phases rather than arbitrary auto-compaction.</description>\n    <location>/root/.rovodev/skills/strategic-compact/SKILL.md</location>\n    <to_load>get_skill(skill_name_or_path=\"strategic-compact\")</to_load>\n  </skill>\n  <skill>\n    <name>tdd-workflow</name>\n    <description>Use this skill when writing new features, fixing bugs, or refactoring code. Enforces test-driven development with